# K-SCAN | MASTER ARCHITECT RULES
# Role: Senior Mobile Engineer & AI Architect
# Project: K-SCAN (Luxury Fashion AI)
# Theme: Obsidian (Black/White/Silver, high-contrast, editorial minimalist)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. DESIGN LANGUAGE — OBSIDIAN THEME
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# Palette
# Background:       #000000 (primary), #0A0A0A (surface), #111111 (elevated)
# Text:             #FFFFFF (primary), #A0A0A0 (secondary), #666666 (tertiary)
# Accent:           #C0C0C0 (silver), #E8E8E8 (highlight)
# Borders:          rgba(255,255,255,0.08)
# Error:            #FF3B30
# Success:          #34C759

# Typography
# Primary:          Inter (weights: 300 Light, 400 Regular, 500 Medium, 600 SemiBold)
# Display:          System Serif (for hero/result headlines only)
# Sizing:           12px body, 14px labels, 20px section heads, 32px display

# Spacing System
# Base unit:        8px
# Component gaps:   16px (tight), 24px (standard), 32px (section), 48px (major)
# Screen padding:   horizontal 24px, vertical safe-area + 16px

# Motion
# Duration:         200ms (micro), 350ms (standard), 500ms (emphasis)
# Easing:           cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1.0)
# Rule:             ALL animations must use `useNativeDriver: true`

# Aesthetic Principles
# - Minimalist luxury. Large whitespace, restrained motion.
# - NO generic Material UI / Android patterns.
# - NO default system alerts, modals, or toasts. All feedback is custom UI.
# - NO bright accent colors. Everything lives in the black/white/silver range.
# - NO drop shadows on dark backgrounds. Use border + elevation via opacity shifts.


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. TECHNICAL STACK
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# Frontend
# - React Native (Expo SDK 52+)
# - Expo Router (file-based routing)
# - expo-camera (CameraView component)
# - react-native-reanimated (for complex animations)

# Backend
# - Expo API Routes (`+api.ts` / `+api.js` files in app/ directory)
# - Local Node.js server for development

# AI Model
# - Gemini 2.0 Flash (vision-capable)
# - Endpoint: Google Generative AI REST API
# - API key stored in .env as GEMINI_API_KEY (never hardcoded)


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. CONNECTIVITY & NETWORKING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# Dynamic IP Configuration
# API calls MUST read the base URL from environment:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.XX:8081
#
# In code, always reference:
#   const API_BASE = process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL || 'http://localhost:8081';
#
# NEVER hardcode an IP address or port in component files.

# Port Fallback Strategy
# The dev server may run on 8081 or 8082 (Expo default port conflict).
# Implement a health-check utility in services/api.ts:
#
#   async function resolveApiBase(): Promise<string> {
#     const base = process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL || 'http://localhost';
#     for (const port of [8081, 8082]) {
#       try {
#         const res = await fetch(`${base}:${port}/api/health`, { timeout: 2000 });
#         if (res.ok) return `${base}:${port}`;
#       } catch {}
#     }
#     throw new Error('K-SCAN backend unreachable on 8081 or 8082');
#   }
#
# Cache the resolved URL for the session. Do not re-check on every request.

# API Response Shape (all /api/analyze endpoints)
# {
#   "result": "string — detailed AI fashion analysis text",
#   "metadata": {
#     "category": "string",
#     "color": "string",
#     "silhouette": "string",
#     "confidence": "number (0-1)"
#   }
# }


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. STATE MACHINE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# Every scan interaction follows this state machine exactly.
# Each state has a defined UI treatment. Do not invent intermediate states.

# State          | UI Behavior
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# idle           | Viewfinder visible. L-corners static. "Scan" CTA pulsing subtly.
# capturing      | Shutter flash (100ms white overlay, opacity 0→0.6→0). Haptic light.
# processing     | Scanning line animates vertically. Skeleton card slides up at 30% opacity.
# result         | Glassmorphism card slides up with analysis. Metadata chips appear staggered.
# error          | Card slides up with error message + "Retry" CTA. No system alerts.

# Transitions:
# idle → capturing:    User taps scan button
# capturing → processing: Image captured successfully
# processing → result:   API returns 200
# processing → error:    API returns non-200 OR network timeout (8s)
# result → idle:         User taps "Scan Again" or swipes card down
# error → idle:          User taps "Retry"
# error → idle:          Auto-dismiss after 10s


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. CRITICAL COMPONENTS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Viewfinder ──
# Custom L-shaped corners drawn with absolute-positioned Views.
# Corner size: 28px arm length, 3px stroke width, color #FFFFFF.
# Corner inset: 32px from each edge.
# Scanning line: horizontal, full-width of viewfinder, 2px height, color rgba(255,255,255,0.7).
# Animation: translateY top-to-bottom, 2s duration, linear, infinite loop.
# MUST use useNativeDriver: true.

# ── Glassmorphism Analysis Card ──
# Container:
#   backgroundColor: rgba(10, 10, 10, 0.85)
#   borderRadius: 24px
#   borderWidth: 1px
#   borderColor: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1)
#   backdropFilter: blur(20px)  — use @react-native-community/blur or expo-blur
#   paddingHorizontal: 24px
#   paddingVertical: 28px
#
# Slide-up animation:
#   From: translateY(screenHeight * 0.4), opacity 0
#   To:   translateY(0), opacity 1
#   Duration: 500ms
#   Easing: cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1.0)
#   MUST use useNativeDriver: true
#
# Content layout:
#   - Category label: 12px, Inter 500, #666666, uppercase, letterSpacing 2
#   - Result headline: 20px, Inter 600, #FFFFFF, marginTop 8
#   - Analysis body: 14px, Inter 400, #A0A0A0, marginTop 16, lineHeight 22
#   - Metadata chips: horizontal row, marginTop 20, gap 8
#     Each chip: paddingH 12, paddingV 6, borderRadius 100, border 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.12)
#     Chip text: 12px, Inter 400, #C0C0C0
#   - "Scan Again" CTA: full-width, height 48, borderRadius 12, bg #FFFFFF, text #000000
#     Font: 14px, Inter 600. marginTop 24.

# ── Error Card ──
# Same glassmorphism container as Analysis Card.
# Icon: SF Symbol or custom "!" in circle, 40px, color #FF3B30.
# Title: "Analysis Failed", 18px Inter 600 #FFFFFF.
# Message: error description, 14px Inter 400 #A0A0A0.
# CTA: "Retry" button, same style as "Scan Again".


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. CAMERA SAFETY
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# ALWAYS check permissions before mounting CameraView:
#   const [permission, requestPermission] = useCameraPermissions();
#   if (!permission?.granted) → show permission request UI (custom, not system)
#
# Handle permission states:
#   - undetermined: Show branded permission prompt with explanation
#   - denied: Show settings redirect with explanation
#   - granted: Mount CameraView
#
# NEVER mount <CameraView> before permission is confirmed granted.


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. CODE ARCHITECTURE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# File Structure:
# app/
#   index.tsx              — Main scan screen (lean: UI + state wiring only)
#   +api/
#     analyze+api.ts       — Gemini API route
#     health+api.ts        — Health check endpoint (returns { status: "ok" })
# hooks/
#   useScanState.ts        — State machine logic (idle/capturing/processing/result/error)
#   useViewfinderAnimation.ts — Scanning line animation
#   useCardAnimation.ts    — Slide-up/dismiss animation
# services/
#   api.ts                 — resolveApiBase(), analyzeImage(base64)
#   gemini.ts              — Gemini API call wrapper
# components/
#   Viewfinder.tsx         — L-corners + scanning line
#   AnalysisCard.tsx       — Glassmorphism result card
#   ErrorCard.tsx          — Glassmorphism error card
#   MetadataChip.tsx       — Individual metadata tag
#   ScanButton.tsx         — Capture CTA with pulse animation
# constants/
#   theme.ts               — All colors, spacing, typography, motion values
# types/
#   scan.ts                — ScanState, AnalysisResult, ApiResponse types

# Principles:
# - app/index.tsx should be <80 lines. All logic lives in hooks/services.
# - Every color, spacing value, and animation duration comes from constants/theme.ts.
# - No inline styles for values that exist in the theme.
# - TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types.
# - All API calls go through services/api.ts, never called directly from components.


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 8. PERFORMANCE RULES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# - ALL Animated.* calls must set useNativeDriver: true.
# - Image capture: use base64 output from expo-camera, compress to quality 0.7.
# - API timeout: 8 seconds. If exceeded, transition to error state.
# - Memoize expensive components with React.memo.
# - No unnecessary re-renders: useScanState should return stable references.
# - Camera preview must maintain 30fps minimum. No JS-thread-blocking during preview.


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# 9. THINGS YOU MUST NEVER DO
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# - NEVER use Alert.alert() or any system dialog. All feedback is in-app custom UI.
# - NEVER hardcode IP addresses or ports in component/hook files.
# - NEVER use Material UI / Paper / default RN component libraries for UI elements.
# - NEVER use bright or saturated colors outside the Obsidian palette.
# - NEVER skip the error state. Every API call must handle failure gracefully.
# - NEVER leave console.log in production code. Use __DEV__ guard or remove.
# - NEVER store API keys in source files. Always use .env + expo-constants.
# - NEVER mount CameraView without confirmed permission.
# - NEVER use Animated without useNativeDriver: true.
